snippet.textDisplay:
Is it possible that Nvidia is using all these weird trademark and patent applications to distract people and mislead them into believing Nvidia is using so-and-so technology/architectures while the actual product name has been registered alongside all the fake ones, while only using one of the technology registered? 

Patent and trademark registration relatively isn't that expensive, and given their marketing budget it'd be a drop in the bucket compared to the benefit of disorienting their rivals into wasting even more resources towards multiple research paths at once to compete.
